    <header>
        <h1><span class="title" itemprop="name" data-bind="text:title">Great British Romance</span></h1>
    </header>

    <img class="picture pull-right img-responsive" itemprop="image" data-fieldname="picture" src="/media/cache/75/fc/75fce59754cb6155b5bdc3c1ba5435ba.jpg" width="400" height="566" data-src="/static/img/events/ROMANCE_POSTER_WEB_REVISED_1.jpg" data-width="400" data-height="566" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#img-picture-781" alt="" data-bind="attr: { src: pictureData().displaySrc, width: pictureData().displayWidth, height: pictureData().displayHeight, 'data-src': pictureData().src, 'data-width': pictureData().width, 'data-height': pictureData().height }" /><div class="modal " id="img-picture-781">    <div class="modal-dialog">        <div class="modal-content">            <div class="modal-header">                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">                    &times;                </button>            </div>            <div class="modal-body">                <img src="/static/img/events/ROMANCE_POSTER_WEB_REVISED_1.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="" data-bind="attr: {src: pictureData().displaySrc}">            </div>        </div>    </div></div>

    <h3><time class="startDate" datetime="2011-09-11" data-bind="attr:{datetime:startDateTime()},text:displayStart()">Sunday 11</time> to <time class="endDate" datetime="2011-09-22" data-bind="attr:{datetime:endDateTime()},text:displayEnd()">Thursday 22 September 2011</time></h3>

    <meta itemprop="image" content="/media/cache/75/fc/75fce59754cb6155b5bdc3c1ba5435ba.jpg">

    <div class="bodysection">
        <div class="body" itemprop="about" data-fieldname="body" data-bind="htmlValue:body">
<p><strong>It's time to celebrate a very British kind of romance!  </strong></p>
<p>The Star and Shadow presents four films - two period dramas, two contemporary to production -  that straddle WWII and span the country.</p>
<p>These films will break your heart in a rather matter-of-fact, stiff upper-lipped, brooding way.  There's little scope for a happy ending when it comes to Great British Romance!</p>

<p><em>Price for each film is £5 (full price) / £3.50 (concessions) OR £4.50 advance tickets online here </em><a href="http://www.wegottickets.com/searchresults"><em>http://www.wegottickets.com/searchresults</em></a></p>
</div>
    </div>

    </div>

    <header class="row">
        <h3></h3>
    </header>

    <div class="smallsublist">
        <header>
            <h3>Films in the Great British Romance:</h3>
        </header>
        
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxb mo0911"
                     data-href="/on/film/832">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/8b/af/8bafd0709c4f95dfe79c54f0dfc139bf.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/79/2e/792e4f7daed50fc4a729b556fee1dddc.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">11</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/832">Wuthering Heights (1939)</a></h1>

                <h2>11 Sep 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Our Great British Romance season begins with one of the greatest love stories ever told. Laurence Olivier, Merle Oberon and David Niven star in this classic tale of doomed love upon the Moors.  Heathcliff, it's me, Cathy!</p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/832">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxa mo0911"
                     data-href="/on/film/833">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/10/05/1005fc67f52b75338317e91245ea0ff3.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/4c/ad/4cad37b9cc283783d13f0b2e7f778ae3.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">15</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/833">I Know Where I&#39;M Going! (1945)</a></h1>

                <h2>15 Sep 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Powell and Pressburger most certainly know how to do romance!  Wendy Hiller is magnificent as the unromantic and stubborn Joan Webster who is out to marry for marriage's sake, but who finds love along the way.</p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/833">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxb mo0911"
                     data-href="/on/film/834">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/72/79/727904d2e66768dd06775271f8be36d5.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/29/68/29689fc6181243a3ea3d15f515c23e6d.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">18</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/834">The Wicked Lady (1945)</a></h1>

                <h2>18 Sep 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>A Gainsborough picture to shock and break your heart.  Barbara Worth (Margaret Lockwood) meets her match in Captain Jerry Jackson (James Mason) in a film of dandy highway men, dissatisfaction and desire.</p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/834">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxa mo0911"
                     data-href="/on/film/835">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/71/95/719530ac0aae2d9e244c0eaca74f77d9.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/d0/ff/d0ff8cf1b94ede8f57e02d35ec492ed7.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">22</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/835">Brief Encounter (1945)</a></h1>

                <h2>22 Sep 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Our season ends with the ultimate of all Great British Romance films. A chance meeting leads to an impossible love affair, every Thursday, over a cup of tea.  It's GREAT.  It's BRITISH.  It's ROMANCE!</p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/835">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

